This paper proposes a methodology for visualizing and interpreting the hidden state dynamics of Seq2Seq recurrent neural networks. The paper focuses on the application of this methodology to sequence prediction tasks, which are commonly studied in the machine learning subfields of natural language processing and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also utilizes proper orthogonal decomposition, which is a technique commonly used in the subfield of control theory (cs.SD) and neural networks (cs.NE).
